und%2080%25%20of%20its%20traffic%20came%20from%20Google%20searches.%20The%20company%20went%20public%20in%202004%2C%20but%20its%20share%20price%20crashed%20not%20long%20after%2C%20following%20a%20change%20in%20Google's%20algorithm%20that%20decimated%20its%20traffic.%20(Shopping.com%20sold%20to%20eBay%20in%202005.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20starting%20Nextdoor%20with%20my%20cofounders%2C%20we%20said%20it's%20much%20more%20difficult%20to%20grow%20without%20the%20benefit%20of%20Google%2C%20but%20we%20want%20to%20do%20everything%20not%20to%20be%20reliant%20because%20we%20can't%20sleep%20well%20at%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20Tolia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20never%20allowed%20our%20content%20to%20be%20scraped%2C%20to%20be%20distributed%20%E2%80%94%20we%20aren't%20crawled%20by%20any%20of%20the%20search%20engines%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20unusual%20approach.%20Many%20website%20owners%20are%20laser-focused%20on%20how%20their%20brands%20show%20up%20on%20search%20pages%20and%20frequently%20optimize%20their%20sites%20for%20Google's%20crawlers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20approach%20is%20also%20why%20you%20won't%20see%20Nextdoor%20cutting%20a%20licensing%20deal%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-google-search-ai-overview-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EReddit's%20partnership%20with%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20search%20giant%20has%20said%20the%20deal%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20Reuters%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Ftechnology%2Freddit-ai-content-licensing-deal-with-google-sources-say-2024-02-22%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20worth%20about%20%2460%20million%20a%20year%20to%20Reddit%20%E2%80%94%20will%20not%20only%20train%20its%20AI%20models%20but%20surface%20more%20information%20derived%20from%20Reddit%20in%20its%20search%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETolia%20questioned%20the%20long-term%20viability%20of%20these%20sorts%20of%20deals%2C%20even%20if%20they're%20additive%20to%20the%20bottom%20line%20in%20the%20short%20term.%20(Disclosure%3A%20OpenAI%20has%20a%20licensing%20partnership%20with%20BI%20parent%20company%20Axel%20Springer.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETolia%20said%20that%20if%20users%20decide%20to%20go%20to%20Google%20to%20get%20data%20derived%20from%20Reddit%2C%20Google%20could%2C%20over%20time%2C%20drive%20down%20the%20cost%20of%20its%20licensing%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20consumers%20aren't%20even%20going%20to%20know%20it's%20Reddit%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20Tolia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20has%20previously%20said%20that%20its%20AI%20Overviews%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.searchenginejournal.com%2Fgoogle-claims-ai-search-delivers-quality-clicks-despite-traffic-loss%2F547401%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esend%20%26quot%3Bhigher%20quality%26quot%3B%20visits%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20some%20websites%20when%20users%20click%20on%20source%20citation%20links%20for%20more%20information.%20However%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsearchengineland.com%2Fgoogle-ai-overviews-hurt-click-through-rates-454428%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseparate%20analyses%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%20independent%20researchers%20suggest%20that%20AI%20overviews%20can%20hurt%20click-through%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b7ca6161-1c16-4648-b2ca-2eec161a1e13%5C%22%3ENextdoor%20is%20preparing%20for%20its%20next%20era%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETolia's%20stance%20on%20licensing%20doesn't%20mean%20Nextdoor%20doesn't%20have%20AI%20ambitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETolia%20wants%20every%20neighborhood%20on%20Nextdoor%20to%20have%20an%20AI%20agent%2C%20so%20consumers%20can%20ask%20its%20chatbot%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20the%20best%20place%20to%20go%20to%20in%20Marylebone%20for%20a%20great%20Tikka%20Masala%3F%26quot%3B%20Nextdoor's%20agent%20would%20then%20trawl%2014%20years%20of%20users'%20posts%20and%20recommendations%20to%20surface%20an%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt'